members.description: Unable to collect firmware inventory from the server. The firmware inventory in OneView may not be up to date.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: Ensure that the network connectivity to the iLO is in a healthy condition. The health can be viewed from the server hardware page. If there are any active alerts in the server hardware activity page, follow the resolutions specified in them. Refresh the server in order to fetch the inventory again. If the problem persists, contact your authorized support representative and provide them with a OneView support dump and the AHS logs from the iLO.

members.description: The port map, virtual identifier, or server location information may not be up-to-date in the iLO.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: This does not affect the appliance, but it may prevent HPE Insight Control server provisioning or NIC configuration in the iLO UI from operating correctly.  If you are not using these applications, you may clear the alert.  Otherwise, try resetting the iLO and then refresh the server hardware.

members.description:
Unable to configure single sign-on (SSO) settings on the iLO at fe80:0:0:0:af1:eaff:fe71:a130%bond0, which are required to launch the iLO web interface and Java console without credentials.
Unable to find valid certification for requested remote host.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: The iLO might have reached the maximum number of certificates it can store.  Login to iLO at fe80:0:0:0:af1:eaff:fe71:a130%bond0 to remove any unneeded SSO certificates.  Reset the iLO and refresh the server hardware. If the problem persists, contact your authorized support representative and provide them with a support dump.
